I’ve implemented the two requested endpoints. Before using them, please follow the steps below:

1. Create at least two users in the database using the user signup API:
   http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/users/signup

2. Since work details (work entries, durations, and hourly rates) require additional data, the necessary supporting
   APIs would normally be needed.
   To simplify this for now, I’ve created a seed endpoint that generates test data for users along with their
   work durations.
   Please use the following URL and run it only once:
   http://127.0.0.1:8000/docs#/worklogs/worklogs-seed_test_data

3. Once the above step is completed and dummy data is created, you’re all set to use the requested endpoints.



----------------------------  API Usage Guide -----------------------------------------------------
1. NAME: list-all-worklogs
   CURL: curl -X 'GET' \
  'http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/worklogs/list-all-worklogs' \
  -H 'accept: application/json'

  DOC: http://127.0.0.1:8000/docs#/worklogs/worklogs-list_all_worklogs

  RESPONSE: [
        {
        "task_name": "Build Login Page",
        "description": "Frontend login implementation with validation",
        "id": "8811d4d8-3d55-4e6b-828c-1946cdaee8d9",
        "user_id": "d09e368e-f809-4554-9c6f-534cd10bff25",
        "created_at": "2026-02-02T08:41:03.259392",
        "updated_at": "2026-02-02T08:41:03.259456",
